 their own undoing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotherhood in popular culture. 0aMotherhoodxPsychological aspects. 0aMotherhoodxSocial aspects. 0aMotherhood. 0aMothersxPsychology. 0aMothersxSocial conditions. 0aMothers. 0aWorking mothersxPsychology. 0aWorking mothersxSocial conditions. 0aWorking mothers. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311127253508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020z978311127473708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311141765340uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486463340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774864633423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774864633/original  a978-3-11-127253-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-127473-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-141765-3  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles